24/08/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The ten Macedonian soldiers who served in the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan returned home Friday (22 August) after their six-month mission.
Army Chief of Staff Gen Metodi Stamboliiski welcomed the soldiers at the airport in Skopje, saying that Macedonia had taken a significant step forward with regard to participation in international peacekeeping missions.
A new Macedonian unit left for Afghanistan on 15 August.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 23/08/03;
MIA - 22/08/03)
